More Fool Me by Stephen Fry -- digested Read
(Guardian, John Crace)
http://www.theguardian.com/books/2014/oct/12/more-fool-me-stephen-fry-digested-read
--> that's already a secondary representation, and it assumes Fry's first-person narrator's voice (i.e. identity?) --> further defamiliarise by using it in tertiary representation: John Crace, U r Fry. "Should I plunge straight into the mephitic swamp of my cocaine years, or should I spend the first 100 pages rehashing the first two volumes of my autobiography?"
It also has some third-person bits: " What has silly old Stephen gone and done now?"

